# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FILE         : .trivyignore
# DESCRIPTION  : Documents intentional Trivy scan exceptions.
#                Every exception has a documented justification.
#                Review this file quarterly.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# AVD-AWS-0104 — Security group allows egress to 0.0.0.0/0
# Justification: EC2 instances require outbound internet access for
# OS security patches via NAT Gateway. Inbound access is strictly
# controlled via SG-to-SG referencing (not CIDR blocks).
# AVD-AWS-0104

# AVD-AWS-0178 — ALB does not drop invalid headers
# Justification: HTTP-only listener for Free Tier demonstration.
# Production upgrade path: HTTPS listener with ACM certificate.
# AVD-AWS-0178

# AVD-AWS-0053 — RDS publicly accessible
# Justification: publicly_accessible = false is set explicitly.
# This finding is a false positive — verify in modules/rds/main.tf.
# AVD-AWS-0053
